byline.contributor: Nick Cumming-Bruce contributed reporting from Geneva.

abstract: Finnish authorities arrest Iraqi twins suspected of belonging to Islamic State and executing 11 unarmed prisoners in Iraq; men entered country seeking asylum, raising concerns that flow of immigrants into Europe form Middle east contains jihadists.
lead_paragraph: The arrests announced on Thursday threatened to fan an already simmering anti-immigrant backlash in Finland and Europe as a whole.

headline.main: Finnish Police Arrest Iraqi Twins Linked to ISIS Massacre in 2014
